article.headline: UNC-Greensboro 75, Coll. of Charleston 67
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Mikko Koivisto scored a career-high 25 points, Kyle Hines added 23 points and North Carolina-Greensboro beat the College of Charleston 75-67 on Monday night. Kevin Oleksiak added 22 points for the Spartans (16-11, 10-8 Southern Conference), who had three 20-point scorers for just the second time since they moved to Division I and first time since a loss to North Carolina State last January. UNC Greensboro shot 84 percent in the second half, making the first 10 shots of the second half to erase a seven-point deficit. Hines has reached double figures in scoring in 77 straight games for UNC Greensboro, which clinched a bye in the Southern Conference tournament. Jermaine Johnson had 18 points to lead the Cougars (12-16, 7-11). Andrew Goudelock added 12 and Donovan Monroe finished with 11.
